-- Australia shares seen inching higher underpinned by Wall St, metals prices
-- 
-- Wed Jul 16, 2014 06:27PM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, July 17 (Reuters) - Australian shares are seen posting modest gains on Thursday as Wall Street edged higher and the Dow Jones ended at a record high close, while an uptick in metals prices may support mining stocks.

Local share price index futures <YAPcm1> added 0.2 percent, but was a 34.9-point discount to the underlying S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> close. The benchmark added 0.1 percent on Wednesday. * New Zealand's benchmark NZX 50 index <.NZ50> slipped 0.1 percent in early trade. * U.S. stocks rose overnight with the Dow Jones industrial average closing at a record high, boosted by the latest merger news and some strong corporate earnings. [.N] * Aluminium touched its highest levels in 16 months after data showed a stronger economic growth in top metals consumer China amid producer cutbacks and eroding inventories. * Gold rebounded after two consecutive days of sharp losses, but a strong U.S. economic outlook and fears that the Federal Reserve could raise U.S. interest rates limited gains for the safe haven.  * Woodside Petroleum Ltd <WPL.AX> is due to release its second-quarter report later in the day.-------------------- MARKET SNAPSHOT @ 2220 GMT ---------------- INSTRUMENT   LAST   PCT CHG   NET CHG S&P 500 <.SPX>   1,981.57 0.42% 8.290 USD/JPY <JPY=>   101.64  -0.03%-0.030 10-YR US TSY YLD<US10YT=RR>  2.5305  --  #N/A SPOT GOLD   <XAU=>   1,298.74-0.01%-0.130 US CRUDE<CLc1>   101.46   0.26% 0.260 DOW JONES   <.DJI>   17,138.200.45% 77.52 ASIA ADRS   <.BKAS>  151.32   0.11%  0.17 ----------------------------------------------------------------  * Wall St Gains on M&A, results; Dow ends at record highs [.N]  * U.S. crude rises over $1 after sharp stockpile fall [O/R]  * Gold rebounds on bargain hunting after two-day tumble  [GOL/]  * Aluminium hits 16-mo high as China data lifts outlook [MET/L]  DIARIES & DATA:  U.S. earnings diary  [RESF/US]Wall Street Week Ahead   [.N/O]  Eurostocks Week Ahead  [.EU/O] ................................................................ For latest top breaking news across all markets  [NEWS] ................................................................ TOP NEWS SUMMARIES ON OTHER SUBJECTS | U.S. Companies [TOP/EQU] | European Companies  [T